9
00:00:50,799 --> 00:00:52,919
Here’s how it works in business…

10
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:58,090
A few months ago, I had built a website and
was getting my visitors from social media,

11
00:00:58,090 --> 00:01:04,019
like Reddit, Pinterest, Twitter, and other
social media and forums. In fact, this took

12
00:01:04,019 --> 00:01:09,780
so much time that I was unable to write as
many articles as I wanted to. So I decided

13
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:16,780
I was going to make the process more efficient.
I looked into my data and guess what I found?

14
00:01:16,799 --> 00:01:23,799
For every 1000 visitors I got from Reddit,
I got only about 60 from Pinterest, 20 from

15
00:01:23,909 --> 00:01:30,679
Twitter, and a few more 20s from other forums
and social media. I thought I’m an idiot,

16
00:01:30,680 --> 00:01:36,530
I’m spending the same amount of time on
all these platforms yet look at the results.

17
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:42,370
So I basically completely cut out the ones
with the least effect, and it freed up so

18
00:01:42,370 --> 00:01:48,590
much time for me to write actual articles
that people were interested in. And that made

19
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:53,320
a huge difference in how my website performed.

20
00:01:53,319 --> 00:01:56,029
Now let’s take a look at social interactions…

21
00:01:56,030 --> 00:02:02,879
In college, I dedicated roughly the same amount
of time to the top ten people I hung out with.

22
00:02:02,879 --> 00:02:08,368
But I realized that the majority of the value
and happiness brought into my life only came

23
00:02:08,368 --> 00:02:14,009
