“I’m an idiot. What am I doing?” I decided

24
00:02:14,009 --> 00:02:19,780
to dedicate my time to the two or three of
those people, and that freed up so much time

25
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:25,419
for me to read, meditate, go to the gym, and
to really develop myself.

26
00:02:25,419 --> 00:02:28,030
Let’s look at relationships…

27
00:02:28,030 --> 00:02:34,419
A boyfriend or a husband comes home from work.
After five hours of spending time with her

28
00:02:34,419 --> 00:02:40,458
girlfriend or wife, she complains, “You
don’t spend any time with me!” The guy

29
00:02:40,459 --> 00:02:47,459
has no idea what is going on. He just spent
five hours with this woman. But did he really?

30
00:02:47,848 --> 00:02:53,289
In those five hours even though he talked
to her and was physically with her, his focus

31
00:02:53,289 --> 00:03:00,289
was also on watching TV half of the time and
the rest, checking his Facebook and his phone.

32
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:06,289
Another guy could have worked longer hours,
come home and only spent an hour, literally

33
00:03:06,289 --> 00:03:11,799
a single hour, with her and she would never
complain, because he would make that one hour

34
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,900
all about her.

35
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:20,900
And that is the 80/20 principle applied to
business, social interactions, and relationships.

36
